						               													<description>We cannot keep silent about what we have seen and heard.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pentecost&amp;eacute;s is a game for both young people and adults where the book of the acts of the apostles covers by theme and narrative, in which each player must represent an apostle witness to the resurrection and assumption of Jesus Christ who will have to announce and testify to the message of the good news and to be forming their Christian communities encompassing the people of the different social classes of all the people of Israel in that historical period.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who has been the emissary with the highest score at the end of the game, adding the points of the cards of each community, plus the additional scores, will become the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The objective of the game is to have accumulated the highest score at the end of the game. Where not only will win the one who accumulated the highest score in the community cards, but also the additional scores of the teaching of Jesus Christ and life goal that each of the players will have will be credited.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round, each player has their turn to perform two actions that allow him to:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Obtain Speech tokens: Do conversion actions with God to obtain tokens, to be used soon to obtain community cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Proclaim a card: Once you have the corresponding amount of tokens to exchange for one of the available cards, pay the corresponding cost for it to obtain the card you want.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Baptize a card: Once a community card is obtained, it goes on to add points. Now you can baptize it by paying the amount of corresponding baptismal tokens; and thus enhance your game for later.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends once the community deck cards are used up, so there are no cards left to replace on the table. Each player starting with the starting player will have a last turn, where this time he will have the opportunity to do 3 actions to end his game and move on to the summation of points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
